 g_gc_info_table[gc_info_index] = gc_info;
 ReleaseStore(reinterpret_cast<int*>(gc_info_index_slot), index);
 }
```
In this fix, the `MutexLocker` object is used to lock the `mutex` before accessing the `gc_info_index_slot` variable and unlock it afterward. This ensures that only one thread can modify or read the variable at a time, preventing race conditions.<|im_end|>

